MCAs skipped the Fourth Devolution Conference in Naivasha for lack of proper planning, laxity and ignorance.&ldquo;They had not adopted the calendar to enable them to adjourn the House for a week to attend the conference,&rdquo; deputy speaker Ken Ngondi said.Standing Orders require the MCAs to pass a calendar in the first week of every session. They resumed the session on February 14.Clerk Jacob Ngwele said all House business, including adjournments, must be based on the calendar.&ldquo;They were supposed to pass the calendar and the adjournment motion last week on Thursday to enable them attend the conference, but there was no quorum,&rdquo; he said. Ngwele said Sh10 million released for the MCAs&rsquo; facilitation at the conference has been diverted to salaries.